news.title: Odisha extends deadline for property return submission by officials to April 30
news.para: ​The General Administration and Public Grievances Department in a circular to all Departments, Revenue Divisional Commissioners and District Collectors, said that the officials must submit their annual property return for the period from January 1, 2021 to December 31, 2021.

news.title: Jaipur development body drafts land-use plan for scrapped greenfield airport
news.para: The civic body has not only earmarked the area for residential, institutional, commercial and mixed-use purposes, but it has also reserved 200 bigah for the development of new industrial areas.

news.title: Hines partners with DNR group to develop 2 million sq ft office project in Bengaluru
news.para: The project 'DNR Nagavara' will be developed on a 11.3 acre land parcel and is located in an established micro market adjacent to Manyata Tech Park and Karle Town Centre in North Bengaluru.

news.title: Dwarka expressway stretch in Gurugram may open in December
news.para: The 10.1km-long portion of the expressway in Delhi on which work began after nearly a year of construction on the Gurugram stretch will take longer to complete.

news.title: Office leasing grows 97% to about 11.4 million sq ft in Q1 2022: Report
news.para: Bengaluru, Chennai and Delhi-NCR dominated absorption during the quarter, accounting for almost two-thirds of the transaction activity.

news.title: Punjab, Haryana, Chandigarh admin to discuss land use, high-rise buildings
news.para: The UT adviser had held a meeting with officers of both the state governments last month, a prelude to the upcoming brainstorming to find solutions to the main problems.

news.title: Homes turn dearer in Andhra Pradesh as construction cost rises
news.para: The real estate sector was hit hard by the pandemic. Now, a steep jump in prices of raw materials has compounded the woes of developers. The price rise has lead to homes getting costlier in Vizag and Vijayawada.

news.title: Godrej Industries launches Godrej Capital, to invest Rs 1,500 crore
news.para: Godrej Capital is a subsidiary of GIL and is the holding entity for Godrej Housing Finance (an HFC) and Godrej Finance (an NBFC). It aims to build Rs 30,000 crore balance sheet by 2026.

news.title: Telangana government says Dharani pendency just 6.38%
news.para: ​The Rangareddy district administration finally restored it as patta land after valid proofs and field reports. RR district, which has one of the highest land values in the state, had received 1.25 lakh grievances and applications.

news.title: Varanasi: VDA sets up teams to inspect 174 buildings, give report in seven days
news.para: The first group housing project’s map was sanctioned by VDA in 1984 and after that 174 group housing and apartments have come up so far, said Duhan providing a ward-wise list.

news.title: Lucknow development body to explore 'controlled demolition' technique use
news.para: Known as implosion or controlled demolition, the technique is making headlines in connection with the Noida where twin towers of the Supertech group in sector 93A are to be demolished.

news.title: Isprava Group raises $130 million in funding
news.para: The capital has been raised as a combination of corporate-level equity and project level equity.

news.title: Vijayawada: Builders' bodies protest price rise
news.para: They alleged that cost of paints, iron and cement have increased by nearly 30% in the last 20 days and demanded the state government to announce an action plan to reduce the price of building material and help the construction industry tide over the crisis.

news.title: Haryana: Stilt parking causing green cover loss?
news.para: The complaint said this rampant felling was permitted under Haryana’s building bylaws that allowed people to create stilt parking. Gradually, every inch is being concretised in the city, including the periphery of private plots, it said.

news.title: Office vacancies stay stable as companies start bringing staff back
news.para: Gross absorption in the first quarter of the calendar increased almost three times year-on-year (YoY) to 13.0 million sq feet - the highest in two years, according to Colliers.
